        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add Crabfleet workspace adapter",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add `crabbox adapter serve`, a generic authenticated workspace lifecycle API backed by normal Crabbox provider configuration\n- add `crabbox adapter connect`, an outbound ticket-authenticated relay for hosts that cannot accept inbound connections\n- make create, inspect, stop, recovery, external-provider routing, and WebVNC ownership durable and identity-safe across crashes and restarts\n- add an open-source Linux desktop bootstrap with loopback-only VNC/noVNC, plus public setup and operations documentation\n\n## Why\n\nFleet systems should be able to create fully configured Crabbox workspaces without embedding provider-specific lifecycle logic or maintaining a fork. The adapter keeps deployment policy in configuration while the open-source Crabbox process owns lifecycle, recovery, desktop access, and exact provider cleanup.\n\n## Security and configuration\n\n- bearer tokens are loaded from private, no-follow token files and never accepted on argv\n- the outbound relay uses a current-user-owned, peer-verified Unix socket and exposes only the narrow `crabfleet/v1` request surface\n- state, provider identity, process identity, listener ownership, and external routing are validated before reuse or cleanup\n- deployment policy can pin TTL, idle timeout, class, server type, capabilities, concurrency, and connection timeouts\n- the patch contains no deployment-specific provider or organizational configuration\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test -race -p 2 ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go build -trimpath -o /tmp/crabbox-workspace-controller ./cmd/crabbox`\n- Linux and Windows compile-only coverage for the CLI, controller, and external provider packages\n- `npm test --prefix worker`\n- `npm run check --prefix worker`\n- `npm run lint --prefix worker`\n- `npm run format:check --prefix worker`\n- `npm run build --prefix worker`\n- `node --test scripts/*.test.js`\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- structured autoreview, with accepted findings fixed and regression-tested\n",
